r73 | pingu | 2008-07-28 19:09:00 +0200 (lun. 28 juil. 2008) | 13 lines

Binding is finished. Scoped variables and scoped functions
are in separated chunks, so things like that is non-ambiguous:
function foo(foo : integer) : integer;
begin
  foo = 5;
  foo(5);
end
The "foo" function is different than the "foo" variable, so
there isn't a redefinition error.

Moreover, return keywords must be in a function.


